olive oil
1 packet spaghetti
1 leek
1 packet Venison & Beef Mince
1 sachet beef-style stock powder
1 tin tinned cherry tomatoes
20 g butter
1 tomato
1 bag salad leaves
3 clove garlic
1 sachet Nan's Special Seasoning
1 tsp brown sugar
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese
1 drizzle balsamic vinegar

• Bring a medium saucepan of salted water to the boil.
• Cook spaghetti in boiling water until ‘al dente’, 10 minutes.
• Reserve some pasta water (1/2 cup for 2 people / 1 cup for 4 people), then drain spaghetti and return to saucepan. Drizzle with olive oil to prevent pasta from sticking.

TIP: ‘Al dente’ pasta is cooked through but still slightly firm in the centre.

• Meanwhile, thinly slice the white and light green parts of leek. Finely chop garlic.
• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over a medium-high heat.
• Cook leek, stirring, until softened, 4-5 minutes.
• Add venison & beef mince and cook, breaking up with a spoon, until just browned, 3-5 minutes.
• Add garlic and cook until fragrant, 1-2 minutes.

• Add Nan's special seasoning, beef-style stock powder, tinned cherry tomatoes and some reserved pasta water (1/4 cup for 2 people / 1/2 cup for 4 people) and cook, stirring, until slightly reduced, 2-3 minutes.
• Remove from the heat, then add the butter and brown sugar and stir to combine. Season, then add cooked spaghetti and gently toss to combine. Set aside.
• Meanwhile, roughly chop the tomato.
• In a medium bowl, combine a drizzle of balsamic vinegar and olive oil. Add
rocket leaves and tomato, then toss to coat.

TIP: Add a dash more pasta water if the sauce is dry.

• Divide beef, venison and cherry tomato bolognese between bowls.
• Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese. Serve with tomato salad.